On Loyalty Day, President Donald Trump reaffirms allegiance to the principles upon which the United States is built. He emphasizes the dedication to the country and the honor of its unique heritage. The President acknowledges the responsibility of self-governance and praises the United States for upholding the ideals of freedom, equality, and justice. He vows to stand strong against terrorism and lawlessness and expresses gratitude to service members and veterans for their loyalty and dedication. President Trump designates May 1st as Loyalty Day, calling on all Americans to observe the day with appropriate ceremonies and the recitation of the Pledge of Allegiance. He also urges government officials to display the flag of the United States on all government buildings and grounds on that day.